com.k2.Wiget

Class AssembledWiget<F extends WigetFamily<O>,O,W extends Wiget,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.k2.Wiget.AssembledWiget<F,O,W,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    F - The widget family
    O - The output type
    W - The wiget being assembled
    T - The type of data required by the wiget being assembled
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.k2.Expressions.Evaluator, ContainedWiget<O>, WigetParameterEvaluator<W>

    public class AssembledWiget<F extends WigetFamily<O>,O,W extends Wiget,T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements WigetParameterEvaluator<W>, ContainedWiget<O>
    Am assembled wiget represents a wiget within an assembly of wigets Assembled wigets can set values for the wigets parameters and if set they will override the parameter values derived from the wigets typed data source. They also define the contents wigets containers
    Author:
    simon

      • bind

        public AssembledWiget<F,O,? extends Wiget,?> bind(WigetContainer<?> toContainer,
                                                  AssembledWiget<F,O,? extends Wiget,?> sourceAssembly,
                                                  WigetContainer<?> fromContainer)
        Bind the contents of the from container in the source assembly to the given container. All the contents from the container of the source assembly will be included in the output of the bound to container in the order they were added to the from container and sourrounded by contents added to the to container
        Parameters:
        toContainer - The container to bind the from container contents to
        sourceAssembly - The assembled wiget that provides the bound contents for the from container
        fromContainer - The wiget container on the source assemble whose contents will be bound to the to container
        Returns:
        This assembled wiget for method chaining
